{
  "stem": "13469.7",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But of course, this was just after the end of the war, and there weren't many [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] passenger coaches and trains in Germany around anyway.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So perhaps we were lucky to get a train of cattle trucks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But this time, all the doors were open, and we actually enjoyed ourselves on the train.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In fact, most of the time, we sat on top of the train on the roof, which was very interesting when we went through bridges and tunnels and all that sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But life seemed very cheap, and we weren't worried, really.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We had survived so much that we just took all these risks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I remember, we jumped from one coach, one cattle truck to the next cattle truck, from roof to roof, while the train was running.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Don't think I'll do that again, kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But we were mad.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was perhaps a bit like that, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We, we were over the moon, I suppose is the expression these days, in a way, and-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was full of survivors, that train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it took some time to go through Germany, because the tracks were bombed in many places, and we went through bombed-out cities, and all that.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And eventually, we finished up in Holland, in a place that-- until a few years ago, nobody had ever heard of, when I first gave the talk-- Maastricht.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we said, what's Maastricht?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, of course, everybody knows what's Maastrict-- in the southern edge corner of Holland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that's where we arrived.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And all the people who wanted to go back to Holland were unloaded there, and the train went on to Belgium and France with other survivors who went home there.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
